label.value: Stage II Cervical Cancer AJCC v9

label.value: Stage IIA Cervical Cancer AJCC v9

label.value: Stage IIB Cervical Cancer AJCC v9

value.value: Stage IIB includes: T2b, N0, M0. T2b: Tumor with parametrial invasion but not up to the pelvic wall. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 9th Ed.)

label.value: Stage III Cervical Cancer AJCC v9

value.value: Stage III includes: T3, N0, M0. T3: Tumor extending to pelvic sidewall and/or involving the lower third of vagina, and/or causing hydronephrosis or nonfunctioning kidney. The pelvic sidewall is defined as the muscle, fascia, neurovascular structures, and skeletal portions of the bony pelvis. Cases with no cancer-free space between the tumor and pelvic wall by rectal examination are FIGO III. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 9th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIA Cervical Cancer AJCC v9

value.value: Stage IIIA includes: T3a, N0, M0. T3a: Tumor involving the lower third of vagina but not extending to pelvic wall. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 9th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIB Cervical Cancer AJCC v9

value.value: Stage IIIB includes: T3b, N0, M0. T3b: Tumor extending to pelvic wall and/or causing hydronephrosis or nonfunctioning kidney (unless known to be due to another cause). N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 9th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIC Cervical Cancer AJCC v9

value.value: Stage IIIC includes: IIIC1: TX, T0, T1-3, N1, M0; IIIC2: TX, T0, T1-3, N2, M0. TX: Primary tumor cannot be assessed. T0: No evidence of primary tumor. T1: Tumor strictly confined to the cervix (extension to corpus should be disregarded). T2: Tumor invading beyond the uterus but not to the pelvic wall or to lower third of vagina. T3: Tumor extending to pelvic sidewall and/or involving the lower third of vagina, and/or causing hydronephrosis or nonfunctioning kidney. The pelvic sidewall is defined as the muscle, fascia, neurovascular structures, and skeletal portions of the bony pelvis. Cases with no cancer-free space between the tumor and pelvic wall by rectal examination are FIGO III. N1: Tumor with regional lymph node metastasis to pelvic lymph nodes only. N2: Tumor with regional lymph node metastasis to para-aortic lymph nodes with or without positive pelvic lymph nodes.  M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 9th Ed.)

value.value: Stage IIIC1 includes: TX, T0, T1-3, N1, M0. TX: Primary tumor cannot be assessed. T0: No evidence of primary tumor. T1: Tumor strictly confined to the cervix (extension to corpus should be disregarded). T2: Tumor invading beyond the uterus but not to the pelvic wall or to lower third of vagina. label.value: Stage IIIC2 Cervical Cancer AJCC v9

T1: Tumor strictly confined to the cervix (extension to corpus should be disregarded). T2: Tumor invading beyond the uterus but not to the pelvic wall or to lower third of vagina. T3: Tumor extending to pelvic sidewall and/or involving the lower third of vagina, and/or causing hydronephrosis or nonfunctioning kidney. Cases with no cancer-free space between the tumor and pelvic wall by rectal examination are FIGO III. N2: Tumor with regional lymph node metastasis to para-aortic lymph nodes with or without positive pelvic lymph nodes. M0: No distant metastasis. (from AJCC 9th Ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Cervical Cancer AJCC v9

value.value: Stage IV includes: IVA: T4, Any N, M0; IVB: Any T, Any N, M1. T4: Tumor has involved (biopsy-proven) the mucosa of the bladder or rectum, or has spread to adjacent organs. M0: No distant metastasis. M1: Distant metastasis including inguinal lymph nodes, lung, liver, bone, or intraperitoneal metastases. Metastases to pelvic or paraaortic lymph nodes, or vagina are excluded. (from AJCC 9th Ed.)

label.value: Substance of Abuse

value.value: Any substance, including any illegal, prescription, over-the-counter agent or any other compound, used for the purpose other than indicated or used in quantities other than directed. Substances from various drug classes can be abused, such as opioids, amphetamines, analgesics, benzodiazepines, barbiturates, hallucinogens, steroids, tobacco products and alcoholic substances. A substance of abuse may act on the central nervous system (CNS) or can have an effect in other parts of the body and can lead to physical and/or physiological dependence.

label.value: Cervical Cancer pT1b2 TNM Finding v9

label.value: Open Microscopy Environment Tagged Image File Format

value.value: A tagged image file format (TIFF) image file format that contains an Open Microscopy Environment (OME) XML metadata block in the file header for storing microscopy information (pixels and metadata) using the OME Data Model.

label.value: eIF2B

value.value: EIF2B is a heteropentameric complex (alpha, beta, gamma, delta, and epsilon subunits) essential for protein synthesis that catalyzes GDP/GTP exchange of its Eukaryotic Initiation Factor 2 substrate (restores GTP bound EIF2). For EIF2 to perform additional rounds of initiation, it must be recycled by GDP/GTP exchange. Thus, EIF2B sustains translation. EIF2B-epsilon contains a putative nucleotide-binding domain that may be involved in nucleotide exchange.  EIF2B defects cause VWM. (NCI)

label.value: Kallikrein-2

value.value: Kallikrein-2 (261 aa, ~29 kDa) is encoded by the human KLK2 gene. This protein plays a role in proteolysis and vasodilation.
